INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('Canon 01', '1. Seal the outlet ink hole, in the base of the cartridge with a piece of PVC. \r\n2. The orifices are under the cover. Remove it with a sharp metallic element, trying not to damage it or make a 3 m/m orifice, in the top of the cartridge, as show in the figure.\r\n3. Mounts the syringe and fill it with 7 millilitre of the suitable ink. \r\n4. Insert the needle by the filling orifice corresponding to the colour the ink of the syringe, watch figure, and introduce it until half of the cartridge NOTE: the cartridge contains sponge inside, reason why one slight resistance can be found. \r\n5. Very Slowly injects 7 millilitre of ink or until it begins it has to overflow. \r\n6. After the filling, reallocate the cover. \r\n7. Unseal outlet ink hole in the base of the cartridge. \r\n8. Let rest the cartridge, downwards, so that it expels leftover ink  \r\n9. Clean the nozzles with cleaner and tissue that is enclosed');
INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('¿ CAPACIDADES CARTUCHOS ?', 'The cartridges that come with the new printers of all the marks, without exception, bring very little ink. EXAMPLE: the cartridges tricolor usually have capacity between 21 and 27 mililiter. The original one with the machine contains less than half, between 9 either 12 mililiter 3 or 4 by color.');
INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('Consejos recarga Brother', 'ATTENTION: Print without ink deteriorates the nozzles and causes the air intake ! ! .\r\n\r\nIf your printer does not have cartridges with incorporated nozzles, we recommended to have two games of cartridges; This way it will be able to change the empty cartridge by other already recharged, and to thus avoid that the impression nozzles gets dried for being more than 5\r\nminutes without cartridge. \r\nIf you does not have another cartridge, while recharging, the nozzles will dry, after this you will\r\nneed two or three cleaning through the software of the printer.\r\n\r\nIf once recharged the cartridge, when printing does not leave ink, two are the main reasons: Dry nozzles by low use of the printer, or, nozzles obstructed by to have printed without ink. At the following link will find solutions for this problem Dry Ink red Recuperator + Extractor - > Code 3206.\r\n\r\nIntroduce the ink VERY SLOWLY following the instructions that will find in the section, marks and model of the printer. You can consult with our technical service through info@nelosa.net on the diverse forms to inject the ink in the cartridge.\r\n\r\nBe sure of not changing the colors.\r\n\r\nThe air bubbles should not have to be injected in the cartridge, they would produce failures in the impression, or to even deteriorate the cartridge, to avoid to inject the bubbles, uses the system that is detailed in the following Link: ANTIBURBUJAS SYRINGE - > Code 3219.\r\n\r\nFor the cleaning of a dry cartridge by long periods of inactivity or obturated for printing without ink, -> Code 3206 uses RECUPERATOR "DRY-INK".\r\n\r\nAfter filling up the cartridge, this it could drip; Maintain it for 15 minutes vertical, or until it expels the leftover ink, cleaning before installing it. \r\nThe cartridges of the new Epson have a valve that avoids that the ink leaves by the orifices of exit during the charge, but if the cartridge surcharge in excess, the leftover ink will leave by the nozzles.\r\n\r\nIf needs more than two cleaning, for Epson® printer, wait for 5 minutes between cleaning, and closes the application each two cleaning.\r\n\r\nIn most of cartridges, it´s recommendable to let it rest during 1 hour, so the ink arrives to the nozzles, and to even force the ink extraction through the nozzles; In the case of some of the\r\nblack HP cartridges, is due to let rest during 6 hours so that it expels the leftover ink and the inner pressure of the cartridge becomes stabilized, consults to our technical service how recharging this cartridge with facility.\r\n\r\nThe printers with 6 colors, require of an intense charge in the yellow color since, because this is the more spent color.\r\n\r\nThe usual reason why the printer does not recognize the cartridge, is by to have removed the cartridge with the printer switched off, or another method that is not the normal one for the\r\nchange of cartridge, In models MFC 580, 590 and later ones to April of the 2003 of the Brother® printers, is due to fill the small lateral camera of the cartridge so that this it is recognized like plenty. Also it could be by dirt or deterioration of the contacts of the chip, in the cartridges with built-in nozzles.');
