INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('Consejos recarga Epson', 'ATTENTION: Print without ink deteriorates the nozzles and causes the air intake ! ! .\r\n\r\nWe recommended to have two games of cartridges; This way it will be able to change the empty cartridge by other already recharged, and to thus avoid that the impression nozzles gets dried for being more than 5 minutes without cartridge. More information \r\n\r\nIn most of cartridges, it´s recommendable to let it rest during 1 hour, so the ink arrives to the nozzles, and to even force the ink extraction through the nozzles;\r\n\r\nThe printers with 6 colors, require of an intense charge in the yellow color since, because this is the more spent color. \r\n\r\nEpson® and has a chip that has ti de reprogrammed. Epson click here for the reprogramming of the chip. \r\n\r\nThe cartridges of printers C70, C70 Extra, C80, C82, CX3200 and CX5200 require of a a little delicate refill, since they are designed for "not being refilled", follow the instructions step by step and will not have problems. \r\n\r\nEpson´s cartridges have a valve that he avoids that the ink leaves by the orifices of exit of the ink during the charge, but if the cartridge surcharge in excess, the leftover ink will leave\r\nby the nozzles, once put in the printer. More information');
INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('Consejos recarga HP', 'ATTENTION: Print without ink deteriorates the nozzles and causes the air intake ! ! .\r\n\r\nIf once recharged the cartridge, when printing does not leave ink, two are the main reasons: Dry nozzles by low use of the printer, or, nozzles obstructed by to have printed without ink. At the following link will find solutions for this problem Dry Ink red Recuperator + Extractor - > Code 3206. \r\n\r\nIntroduce the ink VERY SLOWLY following the instructions that will find in the section, marks and model of the printer. You can consult with our technical service through info@nelosa.net on the diverse forms to inject the ink in the cartridge.\r\n\r\nBe sure of not changing the colors. \r\n\r\nThe air bubbles should not have to be injected in the cartridge, they would produce failures in the impression, or to even deteriorate the cartridge, to avoid to inject the bubbles, uses the system that is detailed in the following Link: ANTIBURBUJAS SYRINGE - > Code 3219.\r\n\r\nFor the cleaning of a dry cartridge by long periods of inactivity or obturated for printing without ink, -> Code 3206 uses RECUPERATOR "DRY-INK".\r\n\r\nAfter filling up the cartridge, this it could drip; Maintain it for 15 minutes vertical, or until it expels the leftover ink, cleaning before installing it.\r\n\r\nIn most of cartridges, it´s recommendable to let it rest during 1 hour, so the ink arrives to the nozzles, and to even force the ink extraction through the nozzles; In the case of some of the\r\nblack HP cartridges, is due to let rest during 6 hours so that it expels the leftover ink and the inner pressure of the cartridge becomes stabilized, consults to our technical service how recharging this cartridge with facility.\r\n\r\nThe printers with 6 colors, require of an intense charge in the yellow color since, because this is the more spent color. \r\n\r\nThe usual reason why the printer does not recognize the cartridge, is by to have removed the cartridge with the printer switched off, or another method that is not the normal one for the\r\nchange of cartridge. \r\n\r\nIn a cartridge, recharged of type HP 49, if it does not print a color, can have to three causes, \r\n1. When it is the yellow, most probable, is that in the ink conduit that goes of the deposit of ink\r\nto the injectors, there is an air bubble that does not allow the passage of the ink. If you give the return to the cartridge you will see a transparent cover, through which you will be able to\r\nobserve two conduits through where it passes the ink.The longest is the one of the yellow, that goes of end to end of the cartridge. If in that conduit you observe a fat air bubble, that is charge of which it does not print to you, you must remove it. In order to fix to this the most comfortable solution it is to use an extractorv device, that extracts the air and the ink by the injectors. But if you do not have it you can prove to put air to him by above to the deposit. For it you will have to cover well with sticky tape one of both holes of the chapita of plastic transparency that covers the deposit and by the other, with the aid of a syringe, to which you will have connected him a rubber sleeve of a centimeter, and to inject air. \r\n2. If it has recharged the cartridge with much red and quickly in several occasions (it can see that the part of above of the sponge is full of red). In this case which happens to him to the cartridge he is that it has the parched sponge and the filter, this prevents the sweating of the sponge and to the filter it has it clogged. Solution, to remove the sponge and to wash it with istilled water. \r\n3. If the cartridge stains generously of yellow when it is tightened against a paper napkin, but does not print, test to clean the electrical contacts with a suitable cleaner. If this does not work\r\nit is that the cartridge has the deteriorated electrical system and the only thing that you have  left to do she is to throw it.');
