INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('R001', 'The use of printer in house and the office, has been increased in the last years remarkably, unfortunately, the impression through a ink-jet printer can get to be very expensive, specially if its main use is for great amounts of printed graphs, in the past, when a cartridge was emty, the only option that it had was to replace it by one new one. Recently, nevertheless the system of stuffed for cartridges has been possible, offering a saving to them when these are compared with the new cartridges. Like an alternative to that already they were in the market, it nails them of the success of our KIT has been the high quality of our ink and the techniques of filling, facilitated by an extensive information of all the models and marks of printers. The ink that contains Kit NELOSA, is best available one. It is refined until obtaining less than half of one micron and is adapted for the printing more outstanding Ink-jets. The instructions for the different cartridges are updated constantly by our technicians.');
INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('R002', 'In order to avoid that the nozzles get obstructed or deteriorated, refill the cartridge before the ink finishes, when the ink levels indicate between 50% and 70%.\r\n\r\nThe amount of refills will depend on the state of the nozzles, between 8 or 10 times in cartridges with incorporated nozzles ( HP  Lexmark ) and 20 charges or more, the cartridges without incorporated nozzles ( Epson  Canon ); The amount of refills will increase using the Kit for the maintenance and repair of nozzles- > Code 3210.\r\n\r\nATTENTION: Printing without ink deteriorates the nozzles and causes the air bubbles.\r\n\r\nIf once recharged the cartridge, cartridge does not leave ink, two are the main reasons: Dry nozzles for long time with no printing or, nozzles obstructed by have printed without ink. Using Dry Ink red Recuperator + Extractor - > Code 3206, will be able to repair most of these cartridges.\r\n\r\nIntroduce the ink VERY SLOWLY, following the instructions that will find in the section, brand and model of the printer. You can consult with our technical service through info@nelosa.net on the diverse forms to inject the ink in the cartridge.(More Info)\r\n\r\nBe sure of not changing the colours.\r\n\r\nThe air bubbles should not have to be injected in the cartridge, if this happens, they would produce failures in the impression, or even deteriorate the cartridge, to avoid to inject the bubbles, uses the system that is detailed in the following Link: ANTIBURBUJAS SYRINGE - > Code 3219.\r\n\r\nFor the cleaning of a dry cartridge by long periods of inactivity, obstructed to print without ink, > Code 3206 uses RECUPERATOR "DRY-INK"\r\n\r\nAfter refilling the cartridge, this it could drip; Maintain it for 15 minutes vertical until it expels the leftover ink, cleaning before installing it. The new Epson cartridges have a valve that avoids that the ink leaves by the outlet ink hole during the refill, but if the cartridge surcharge in excess, the leftover ink will leave by the nozzles when installed.\r\n\r\nIn most of cartridges, is recommendable to let it rest during 30 minutes, so that the ink arrives at the nozzles, and to even force\r\nthe ink extraction through the nozzles; In the case of some of the black ink cartridges of the printing HP, one is due to let rest during 1 hour so that it expels the leftover ink and the inner pressure of the cartridge becomes stabilized, consults to our technical service how to refill this cartridge with facility.\r\n\r\nThe printers with 5 colours and the black, require of an intense charge in the yellow colour, this is the most spent colour.\r\n\r\nThe usual reason why the printer does not recognize the cartridge, is by to have removed the cartridge with the printer turned off, or another method that is not the normal one for the change of cartridge, or the printer is a Epson® and has a chip that has to be reprogrammed; (More Info)\r\n\r\nIn the Brother® printers, lateral camera of the cartridge that has to be full of ink, for that the printer recognizes the cartridge as full. Also it could be by dirt or deterioration of the contacts of the chip. \r\n\r\nDo not leave the cartridge more than 5 minutes on a porous surface, like a cardboard or chamois, this could drain all the ink of the cartridge, leave it to rest on a plastic surface.\r\n\r\nClean the syringe with water whenever it changes of colour and when finalizing the charge.\r\n\r\nThe ink of remainder, black and colour, can be used like black; If this were mixed with cleaner, can be used to fill up labellers, perforating in the superior part and introducing the ink with the syringe. \r\n\r\nIn order to avoid to stain the ink hands, it uses the gloves that are enclosed, uses as it bases a cardboard or blister of plastic of kit.\r\n\r\nIn order to finalize the charge, once mounted the cartridge, the software of the printer uses to clean the nozzles, later to print a test leaf.\r\n\r\nService of technical attendance info@nelosa.net, we would be thankful indicate to us where I buy kit of charge.');
INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('R003', '<p align="center"><strong><font color="#FF0000">If your Brother printer does not recognice the cartridge, once refilled, as full</font></strong></p><p><font color="#0000FF">Inject ink until triangular diposit gets full, this process will have to be made until the sponge lets absorb ink, of this form the printer will recognize the cartridge as full. </font></p>');
INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('R004', 'Printers EPSON® of last generation, have a difference with the rest of their homologous ones, their cartridges contain a chip, that is not in contact with the enemy with the red, if with the printer, and it is recognized by the Software of the control of the printer. The one that it is not in contact with the enemy with the red, indicates that some does not exist form of which the Chip, Software or nobody can know with exactitude whichever red is in the cartridge. Software is developed so that, once a new cartridge is inserted, an account to the loss begins, defining approximately whichever copies are printing, and with this one information without detail, it is showing a graph that lowers the red level. It can happen that when terminating the cartridge, that this not this using to the 100%. These cartridges are re-usable, if the information contained in the chip activates to them.');
INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('Reactivado nivel tinta en impresoras HP_0', 'In most of printing HP, just removing the cartridge and returning it to its position, the ink levels activate (the printer must be turned). The last models of printing HP, could indicate a low ink level after the charge. So that the ink level shows plenty, follow the instructions next');
INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('Reactivado nivel tinta en impresoras HP_1', '1. Open the cover of the printer so that the cartridges positions in the centre. \r\n2. Retire the cartridge.\r\n3. Position the cartridge so that the contacts sees like in the drawing.\r\n4. Cover with adhesive the contact of the left, marked in blue.\r\n5. Reinstall the cartridge and lowers the cover of the printer, after this the printer can say that there is an\r\nerror in the cartridge, ignores the message, the printer would have to print an alignment leaf. \r\n6. Return to raise the cover and to retire the cartridge, it takes off the adhesive, and this time stick it in the contacts of the right, the marked one in red. \r\n7. Reinstall the cartridge and lowers the cover of the printer, and waits for until it arrives at the parking position. \r\n8. Open the cover, retire the cartridge and take off the adhesive. \r\n9. It is possible that something of ink has been dried in the mall pillows or the connectors, use the cleaner to remove dried ink from the nozzles, before placing it in the printer and supporting it in a cloth so that this he absorbs cleaner \r\n10. Reinstall the cartridge and close the cover.\r\n\r\nAfter these steps, the printer initiated the calibration process, once finalized the ink measurer would have to mark plenty.');
INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('Reactivado nivel tinta en impresoras HP_2', 'If method 1 did not work in its printer, it comes again, but this time using the blue contacts in the step the 2 and red contacts in step 4, according to the figure. ');
INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('Reactivado nivel tinta en impresoras HP_3', 'If method 2 not worked, will need two additional cartridges and the one that you filled up. First, put the cartridge filled up in the printer. Allow that it recognizes the cartridge and that prints an alignment page. Remove that cartridge and place the first additional cartridge. Allow that it recognizes and that prints an alignment page. Remove the first additional cartridge and place the second additional cartridge. Allow that it recognizes and prints a alignment page. Remove the second additional cartridge. Place the filled cartridge into the printer. Now will print an alignment page and the ink level will be readjusted to completely. ');
INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('Reactivado nivel tinta en impresoras HP_4', '1. Refill the cartridge.\r\n2. Press the < and > (also the + and -) at the same time, then release quickly (the panel of the LCD must show the date or the procedure I do not work) \r\n3. In the numeric keypad, presses, in order: 7, 8, 9.\r\n4. A message will appear that it will ask if it wishes to stop the accountant of the ink. Press 1 to accept (you can ignite it later, if she installs a new cartridge, repeating process, pressing 2 when prompted). \r\n\r\nYour ink level gauge is now turned off and can resume printing.');
INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('Reactivado nivel tinta en impresoras HP_5', '1. Refill the cartridge.\r\n2. Press and hold down power button. \r\n3. While holding power button: \r\nPress the button of the cancellation 12 times \r\nPress the button of "Summarizes" 1 time\r\n4. Release power button.\r\n\r\nYour ink level gauge is now turned off and can resume printing.');
INSERT INTO `txt_Eng_no_HTML` VALUES ('Serie 01', '1. Seal the nozzles, in the base of the cartridge with a piece of PVC or a protector of nozzles. \r\n2. The orifices are under the cover. Remove it with a sharp metallic element, trying not to damage it. \r\n3. Mounts the syringe and fill it with 7 millilitre of the suitable ink. \r\n4. Insert the needle by the filling orifice corresponding to the colour the ink of the syringe, watch figure, and introduce it until half of the cartridge NOTE: the cartridge contains sponge inside, reason why one slight resistance can be found. \r\n5. Very Slowly injects 7 millilitre of ink or until it begins it has to overflow. \r\n6. After the filling, reallocate the cover. \r\n7. Unseal outlet ink hole in the base of the cartridge. \r\n8. Let rest the cartridge, downwards, so that it expels leftover ink  \r\n9. Clean the nozzles with cleaner and tissue that is enclosed');
