INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones Canon 01', '<B>1.</B> Seal the outlet ink hole, in the base of the cartridge with a piece of PVC.<BR> \r\n<B>2.</B> The orifices are under the cover. Remove it with a sharp metallic element, trying not to damage it or make a 3 m/m orifice, in the top of the cartridge, as show in the figure.<BR>\r\n<B>3.</B> Mounts the syringe and fill it with 7 millilitre of the suitable ink.<BR> \r\n<B>4.</B> Insert the needle by the filling orifice corresponding to the colour the ink of the syringe, watch figure, and introduce it until half of the cartridge NOTE: the cartridge contains sponge inside, reason why one slight resistance can be found<BR>. \r\n<B>5.</B> Very Slowly injects 7 millilitre of ink or until it begins it has to overflow.<BR> \r\n<B>6.</B> After the filling, reallocate the cover.<BR> \r\n<B>7.</B> Unseal outlet ink hole in the base of the cartridge.<BR>\r\n<B>8.</B> Let rest the cartridge, downwards, so that it expels leftover ink.<BR> \r\n<B>9.</B> Clean the nozzles with cleaner and tissue that is enclosed.<BR>');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones Dry-Ink', 'Dissolves the ink drought in conduits and nozzles of, facilitating the extraction of the remainders.\r\n<BR>\r\n<p align="center">\r\n<b><font color="#FF0000">Dried or obstructed cartridge recuperation instructions:</font></b>\r\n</p>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<B>1.</B> Soak the nozzles during 3 or 4 hours with "DRY INK Recuperator " and dry it with the chamois.\r\n<p align="center">\r\n<img src="../../_images/_RepairIns/_Remojo.jpg" width="177" height="148">\r\n</p>\r\n<B>2.</B> In order to extract 1 millilitre of ink through the nozzles, centre the nozzles of the cartridge in the rubber washer (rectangular), choosing the one that adapts to the nozzles and press the cartridge so that it does not take air.<BR>\r\n<B>3.</B> To extract ink, throw the movable part of the syringe, if the cartridge this in good conditions, would have to appear ink in the nozzles.  \r\n<p align="center">\r\n<img src="../../_images/_RepairIns/My_Vaccum_Mod.jpg" width="213" height="302"></p>\r\n<B>4.</B> Deposit the leftover ink in the boat of recycled, if it does not have remainders of cleaner.\r\n<p align="center"> <img src="../../_images/_RepairIns/_Bote_Recicle.jpg" width="104" height="145">\r\n</p>\r\n<B>5.</B> In order to verify the correct operation of the cartridge, stain a cloth or tissues, with 1 or 3 colours according to is the cartridge of colour, black or Photo, using it like a "rubber seal", must be supported in tissue during less of 3 seconds, thus the colours will not mix and appreciate easily which leaves ink.<BR>\r\n<B>6.</B> In case that some of the colours does not appear stained in the cloth, repeats the process and tries to unblock nozzles soaking it during hours in the cleaner Dry  Ink\r\n<BR>\r\n<p align="center">\r\n<font color="#FF0000"><strong>To consider</strong></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<BR>\r\nRemaining ink mixed with cleaner, can be used for refilling black of labellers.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nIn an inactive cartridge for more than 2 weeks, is very difficult its recovery, due to the ink drought in the internal conduits of the cartridge or in sponge.\r\n<BR><BR> \r\nEven the printing report of the ink existence in the cartridge, this can be empty, deteriorating the nozzles if it is printed without ink.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nWe recommend a periodic refill, to maintain sponges of the cartridge in the best possible state, if it is average plenty, them part of the sponge without ink is dried.\r\n<hr><strong><font color="#FF0000">\r\nPrinters with incorporated nozzles: Epson, Canon, etc.</font></strong>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nFor the obstructed or dry nozzles, with 10 the small syringe of mililiter and the extended fuze of fine end, introduces plunger <a href="3206.php"><B>DRY-INK Recuperator</B></a> in the conduits of passage of the ink.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nPut in soaking the nozzles in the same one I eliminate during 3 or 4 hours, it clarifies with abundant water, dry and fills up the ink conduits with his original color, leaving rests the cartridge, once put in the printer.');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones Epson 01', '<B>1.</B> Seal the outlet ink hole, in the base of the cartridge with a piece of PVC.<BR>\r\n<B>2.</B> Remove the sticker to discover the orifices located in the superior part of the cartridge.<BR>  \r\n<B>3.</B> Mounts the syringe and fill it with 7 millilitre of the suitable ink.<BR> \r\n<B>4.</B> Insert the needle by the filling orifice corresponding to the colour the ink of the syringe, watch figure, and introduce it until half of the cartridge NOTE: the cartridge contains sponge inside, reason why one slight resistance can be found. <BR>\r\n<B>5.</B> Very Slowly injects 7 millilitre of ink or until it begins it has to overflow.<BR> \r\n<B>6.</B> Seal filling holes with adhesive PVC, puncturing it for leaving a small vent.<BR> \r\n<B>7.</B> Unseal outlet ink hole in the base of the cartridge.<BR> \r\n<B>8.</B> Let rest the cartridge, downwards, so that it expels leftover ink. <BR>\r\n<B>9.</B> Clean the nozzles with cleaner and tissue that is enclosed.<BR>');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones Epson 01_C', 'A T E N T I O N\r\n<BR>\r\nSome printers contain a chip in the cartridge, which has to be reprogrammed in each refill; Ask by email the information to reprogram the chip, indicating to us the printer model, and we will facilitate several ways to reprogram the chip of the cartridge.');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones Epson C70', '<B>1.</B> Make a small orifice in the part of the cartridge indicated with circulate yellow. <BR>\r\n<B>2.</B> Court a piece of adhesive of 15 x15 m/m, and stick it the closest as possible to the part of plastic of the needle without stepping on it, to prevent that it is introduced more than necessary and perforates the blue sticker. <BR>\r\n<B>3.</B> Introduce the needle, slightly inclined towards the left (aiming at the sticker) by a small orifice, that is discovered when perforating the blue sticker with taken care of not perforating nor the label, NOR ITS FINGER! Since the first time cost to him to enter a little. <BR>\r\n<B>4.</B> In the case of perforating the label, seal it well, first with an adhesive piece and later, with a fine layer of glue. <BR>\r\n<B>5.</B> Introduce the ink very slowly, some ink bubbles could leave, reason why we recommended works on a plastic surface. <BR>\r\n<B>6.</B> Let rest the cartridge during 10 min, supporting the cartridge on the side in opposition to the one of the chip, later on the chip, and thus successive times. <BR>\r\n<B>7.</B> Once filled up the cartridge, seal the orifice of stuffed with the adhesive that is enclosed, making sure that it is closed well, first with an adhesive piece and later, with a fine layer of glue. <BR>\r\n<B>8.</B> In order to support the good operation the cartridge, it uses the syringe, without the needle, to extract the air of the conduits of the cartridge through the outlet ink hole, which contains a valve that opens when inserting the syringe.\r\n<BR>\r\nNOTE \r\n<BR>\r\nIf perforates the blue label with the syringe, sticks an adhesive piece, later to apply a fine layer of glue.');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones generales', 'In order to avoid that the nozzles get obstructed or deteriorated, refill the cartridge before the ink finishes, when the ink levels indicate between 50% and 70%.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nThe amount of refills will depend on the state of the nozzles, between 8 or 10 times in cartridges with incorporated nozzles ( HP  Lexmark ) and 20 charges or more, the cartridges without incorporated nozzles ( Epson  Canon ); The amount of refills will increase using the <b><a href="3210.php">Kit for the maintenance and repair of nozzles- > Code 3210.</a></b>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<font color=%B4#FF0000%B4><b>\r\nATTENTION: Printing without ink deteriorates the nozzles and causes the air bubbles.\r\n</b></font><<BR><BR>\r\nIf once recharged the cartridge, cartridge does not leave ink, two are the main reasons: Dry nozzles for long time with no printing or, nozzles obstructed by have printed without ink. Using <b><a href="3206.php">Dry Ink Recuperator + Extractor - > Code 3206</a></b>, will be able to repair most of these cartridges.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nIntroduce the ink VERY SLOWLY, following the instructions that will find in the section, brand and model of the printer. You can consult with our technical service through <a href="mailto:info@nelosa.net"><b>info@nelosa.net</b></a> on the diverse forms to inject the ink in the cartridge.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nBe sure of not changing the colours.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nThe air bubbles should not have to be injected in the cartridge, if this happens, they would produce failures in the impression, or even deteriorate the cartridge, to avoid to inject the bubbles, uses the system that is detailed in the following Link: ANTIBURBUJAS SYRINGE - > Code 3219.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nFor the cleaning of a dry cartridge by long periods of inactivity, obstructed to print without ink, > Code 3206 uses RECUPERATOR "DRY-INK"\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nAfter refilling the cartridge, this it could drip; Maintain it for 15 minutes vertical until it expels the leftover ink, cleaning before installing it. The new Epson cartridges have a valve that avoids that the ink leaves by the outlet ink hole during the refill, but if the cartridge surcharge in excess, the leftover ink will leave by the nozzles when installed.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nIn most of cartridges, is recommendable to let it rest during 30 minutes, so that the ink arrives at the nozzles, and to even force\r\nthe ink extraction through the nozzles; In the case of some of the black ink cartridges of the printing HP, one is due to let rest during 1 hour so that it expels the leftover ink and the inner pressure of the cartridge becomes stabilized, consults to our technical service how to refill this cartridge with facility.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nThe printers with 5 colours and the black, require of an intense charge in the yellow colour, this is the most spent colour.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nThe usual reason why the printer does not recognize the cartridge, is by to have removed the cartridge with the printer turned off, or another method that is not the normal one for the change of cartridge, or the printer is a Epson® and has a chip that has to be reprogrammed; (More Info)\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nIn the Brother® printers, lateral camera of the cartridge that has to be full of ink, for that the printer recognizes the cartridge as full. Also it could be by dirt or deterioration of the contacts of the chip. \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nDo not leave the cartridge more than 5 minutes on a porous surface, like a cardboard or chamois, this could drain all the ink of the cartridge, leave it to rest on a plastic surface.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nClean the syringe with water whenever it changes of colour and when finalizing the charge.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nThe ink of remainder, black and colour, can be used like black; If this were mixed with cleaner, can be used to fill up labellers, perforating in the superior part and introducing the ink with the syringe. \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nIn order to avoid to stain the ink hands, it uses the gloves that are enclosed, uses as it bases a cardboard or blister of plastic of kit.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nIn order to finalize the charge, once mounted the cartridge, the software of the printer uses to clean the mall pillows, later to print a test leaf.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nService of technical attendance info@nelosa.net, we would be thankful indicate to us where I buy kit of charge.');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones HP 01', '<B>1.</B> The air pressure within the cartridge this controlled by AERATOR (Aperture C) which must be sealed to avoid that the ink drips during the filled up one, uses an adhesive PVC for this work, also seal the nozzles. <BR>\r\n<B>2.</B> Make the orifice (B) of 3 m/m as show in figure 1: IMPORTANT The opening in the centre of the superior part (a) does not have to be bored. PRECAUTION: inner bag does not have to be perforated. <BR>\r\n<B>3.</B> Mount the syringe and charge it with 10 millilitre of the black ink. Put the cartridge vertical, fill up the ink through opening B. Do not leave the cartridge upon the chamois more than 5 minutes. <BR>\r\n<B>4.</B> Energetically press the walls of the cartridge, without letting press seal the orifice (b) with the adhesive that is enclosed, of this form we obtained the necessary emptiness so that the cartridge does not drip. The ink could drip by the union of the mall pillow and the base of the cartridge until equalize the pressure, must clean the ink until it lets drip. <BR>\r\n<B>5.</B> Unseal opening C and of the nozzles, cleaning them with cleaner and the tissues that are enclosed.<BR>');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones HP 02', '<B>1.</B> Put the cartridge with the nozzles face up, and using a pointed instrument, push the ball that seals to pressure the filling orifice. <BR>\r\n<B>2.</B> Mounts the syringe and fill it with 7 millilitre of the suitable ink.<BR>\r\n<B>3.</B> Inject the ink by the orifice until the ink camera is almost full. <BR>\r\n<B>4.</B> Energetically press the walls of the cartridge, and seal the filling orifice with the ball that is enclosed, does not let press until the filling orifice is sealed, of this form we obtained the necessary emptiness so that the ink is retained in the cartridge.<BR>\r\n<B>5.</B> Clean the nozzles with cleaner and the tissue that are enclosed.');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones HP 03', '<B>1.</B> Seal the nozzles, in the base of the cartridge with a piece of PVC or a protector of nozzles. <BR>\r\n<B>2.</B> The filling holes are located at the top of the cartridge, and are sealed by small plastic plugs, which must be pushed into the cartridge, using a sharp element like a ball-point pen, or pull out with a screw or similar. <BR>\r\n<B>3.</B> Mounts the syringe and fill it with 7 millilitre of the suitable ink. <BR>\r\n<B>4.</B> Insert the needle by the filling orifice corresponding to the colour the ink of the syringe, watch figure, and introduce it until half of the cartridge NOTE: the cartridge contains sponge inside, reason why one slight resistance can be found. <BR>\r\n<B>5.</B> Very Slowly injects 7 millilitre of ink or until it begins it has to overflow. <BR>\r\n<B>6.</B> Seal filling holes with adhesive PVC, puncturing it for leaving a small vent. <BR>\r\n<B>7.</B> Unseal outlet ink hole in the base of the cartridge. <BR>\r\n<B>8.</B> Let rest the cartridge, downwards, so that it expels leftover ink. <BR>\r\n<B>9.</B> Clean the nozzles with cleaner and tissue that is enclosed.');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones HP 04', '<B>1.</B> Cut the sticker to be able to retire the cover of the cartridge.<BR>\r\n<B>2.</B> Serve bag that contains the ink, in the filling orifice, there is a plug, remove using a screw or similar, save it, because it will be necessary later. <BR>\r\n<B>3.</B> Insert the needle by the filling orifice of the corresponding colour to the one of the ink of the syringe, and introduce it until half of the cartridge NOTE: the cartridge contains in its interior a bag which must not be to perforate. <BR>\r\n<B>4.</B> Very Slowly millilitre of ink injects 7 or until this almost full one. <BR>\r\n<B>5.</B> Wait for 3 minutes to that the air bubbles disappear and put the plug, pressing bag slightly so that it leaves the air.');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones Inyector 45_1', '1. Mount the syringe with the needle and extract 20 millilitres of ink.<BR>\r\n2. Retire the needle and mount the syringe in the INK-YECTOR.<BR>\r\n3. Push firmly the syringe, maintaining aligned it with the INK-YECTOR, so that it does not take air by the connection, as it shows the figure. <BR>\r\n4. After to have recharged the ink, extract 1 or 2 millilitres of air from the interior of the cartridge, to finalize, retires the cartridge of the INK-YECTOR.<BR>  \r\n5. Clean with a cloth, the ink that can have left.<BR>  \r\n6. Place the cartridge immediately in the printer, or store it with a nozzles protector to avoid that they are dried.<BR>');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones Inyector 45_2', 'To consider\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nIf is hard to inject the ink into cartridge, by excess of air in this, extract it with the Ink-Yector is necessary. In order to extract air of the cartridge, it places this, with the mall pillows upwards.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nThe remainder ink, can be used like black; If this were mixed with I eliminate cleaner, it can be used to fill up labellers, perforating in the superior part and introducing the ink with the syringe.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nThe impression mall pillows are dried very easily, dry it with cleaner, before placing it in the printer, place the cartridge on a cloth so that this it absorbs the cleaner.');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones para la reactivación del chip_1', '<B>1.</B> When the printer indicates that to one of the cartridges the ink has been exhausted, push the button in the printer for the substitution of the cartridge, until it is positioned in half of its route.\r\n<BR>\r\n<B>2.</B> The cartridge with the exhausted accountant  must be replaced, by another one with the full ink accountant, returning to press the central button so that it reads the content of the chip.\r\n<BR>\r\n<B>3.</B> Without turning off  the printer, push the white piece that is indicated in the photo that corresponds to your printer, with a screwdriver or a ball-point pen, of this form will be able to move the nozzles manually.\r\n<BR>\r\n<B>4.</B> Manually locate the nozzle to half of its route, retire the cartridge that place previously and returns to place the old cartridge, stuffed of ink; Of this form it will be able to copy the content of the chip and to reactivate the accountant, some of the printers, like the C42, C62, etc.  they detect the deceit and they re-establish the ink levels, when switching the printer.\r\n<BR> \r\n<B>5.</B> Give back, manually, the nozzles to its starting point.\r\n<BR> \r\n<B>6.</B> Remember that is necessary, after filling up the cartridge, to let rest the cartridge during 1 hour so that the ink arrives at the nozzles.\r\n<BR>\r\n<B>7.</B> We recommend to refill slightly when the ink level indicates that this in half, in order to avoid air bubbles and nozzles damage.\r\n<BR>\r\n<B>8.</B> Before keeping the cartridge that you use to reactivate the exhausted chip, it covers the outlet ink holes, in the inferior part of the cartridge, with adhesive P.V.C. so that the ink is not dried.');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones para la reactivación del chip_2', 'The cartridge with the accountant of the full chip, does not have because to be new, it can use one old one with the chip reprogrammed with the software that is in Internet.\r\n<BR>\r\nWe have a universal resetter, ask for it at the virtual store\r\nhttp://www.recargas-y-consumibles.net/');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones Reactivado nivel tinta en impresoras HP_0', 'In most of printing HP, just removing the cartridge and returning it to its position, the ink levels activate (the printer must be turned). The last models of printing HP, could indicate a low ink level after the charge. \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nSo that the ink level shows plenty, follow the instructions next');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones Reactivado nivel tinta en impresoras HP_1', '<B>1.</B> Open the cover of the printer so that the cartridges positions in the centre.<BR>\r\n<B>2.</B> Retire the cartridge.<BR>\r\n<B>3.</B> Position the cartridge so that the contacts sees like in the drawing.<BR>\r\n<B>4.</B> Cover with adhesive the contact of the left, marked in blue.<BR>\r\n<B>5.</B> Reinstall the cartridge and lowers the cover of the printer, after this the printer can say that there is an error in the cartridge, ignores the message, the printer would have to print an alignment leaf.<BR> \r\n<B>6.</B> Return to raise the cover and to retire the cartridge, it takes off the adhesive, and this time stick it in the contacts of the right, the marked one in red.<BR> \r\n<B>7.</B> Reinstall the cartridge and lowers the cover of the printer, and waits for until it arrives at the parking position.<BR> \r\n<B>8.</B> Open the cover, retire the cartridge and take off the adhesive.<BR> \r\n<B>9.</B> It is possible that something of ink has been dried in the nozzles or the connectors, use the cleaner to remove dried ink from the nozzles, before placing it in the printer and supporting it in a cloth so that this he absorbs cleaner.<BR>\r\n<B>10.</B> Reinstall the cartridge and close the cover.<BR>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nAfter these steps, the printer initiated the calibration process, once finalized the ink measurer would have to mark plenty.<BR>');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones Reactivado nivel tinta en impresoras HP_2', 'If method 1 did not work in its printer, it comes again, but this time using the blue contacts in the step the 2 and red contacts in step 4, according to the figure. ');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones Reactivado nivel tinta en impresoras HP_3', 'If method 2 not worked, will need two additional cartridges and the one that you filled up. First, put the cartridge filled up in the printer. Allow that it recognizes the cartridge and that prints an alignment page. Remove that cartridge and place the first additional cartridge. Allow that it recognizes and that prints an alignment page. Remove the first additional cartridge and place the second additional cartridge. Allow that it recognizes and prints a alignment page. Remove the second additional cartridge. Place the filled cartridge into the printer. Now will print an alignment page and the ink level will be readjusted to completely. ');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones Reactivado nivel tinta en impresoras HP_4', '<B>1.</B> Refill the cartridge.<BR>\r\n<B>2.</B> Press the < and > (also the + and -) at the same time, then release quickly (the panel of the LCD must show the date or the procedure I do not work) <BR>\r\n<B>3.</B> In the numeric keypad, presses, in order: 7, 8, 9.<BR>\r\n<B>4.</B> A message will appear that it will ask if it wishes to stop the accountant of the ink. Press 1 to accept (you can ignite it later, if she installs a new cartridge, repeating process, pressing 2 when prompted). <BR>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nYour ink level gauge is now turned off and can resume printing.<BR>');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones Reactivado nivel tinta en impresoras HP_5', '<B>1.</B> Refill the cartridge.<BR>\r\n<B>2.</B> Press and hold down power button.<BR>\r\n<B>3.</B> While holding power button: \r\nPress the button of the cancellation 12 times<BR> \r\nPress the button of "Summarizes" 1 time<BR>\r\n<B>4.</B> Release power button.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nYour ink level gauge is now turned off and can resume printing.');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones recarga antiburbujas', 'When recharging the ink without pressure in the cartridge, eliminates the possibility that a bubble prevents the slope of the ink towards the nozzles.\r\n<BR>\r\n<B>1.</B> Connect the needle to the 10 Millilitre antibubbles syringe (the one that has the orifice of 3 m/m between 6 and 7) and extracts 6 millilitre of ink of the armoured bottle, without the ink passes of the orifice done in syringe.<BR>\r\n<B>2.</B> Place the syringe with the needle aiming up and replace it with the fuze, or leave the needle as it is explained down, in a the section A.<BR>\r\n<B>3.</B> Throw of the movable part of the syringe so that it passes the orifice, until the end, and locate the end of the fuze in the orifice of the cartridge to fill up (Figure 1).<BR>\r\n<B>4.</B> The ink will fall by its own weight within the cartridge, when finalizing could overflow. <BR>\r\n<B>5.</B> Raise the syringe, with the numbers upwards, thus we will avoid that the ink fall.<BR>\r\n<B>6.</B> Deposit the leftover ink in the armoured bottle. <BR>\r\n<B>7.</B> Lay the cartridge on a cloth, so that this it absorbs the ink that can have been mixed during the refill. \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nDeferent forms to inject the ink into the cartridge.<BR>\r\nA. Safest, but very slow: Retire the piston, thus it passes the orifice and the air enter into de syringe; The ink will fall by its own weight.<BR>\r\nB. Change the needle by the fuze, with the thumb covering the small orifice of the syringe (Blower pipe), place the syringe in the orifice of the cartridge and controls the exit of the ink.');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones reseteador Universal_0', 'Observe that the resetter, has several notches, which are designed to adapt to several cartridges. Also they contain a plastic piece, which will be used for the Epson Stylus C70,  C80, C80, Stylus Photo 950, 960, 2100 and 2200.');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones reseteador Universal_1', '1. Centre the cartridge in the corresponding notch, so that per to us they contact with the chip (Figure 1).<BR> \r\n2. Place the faced resetter and the cartridge, so that per of resetter touch the chip to us of the cartridge. The green light will blink when the reset finalizes. \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nIn order to reset the Epson Stylus C70, C80, C80, Stylus Photo 950, 960, 2100 and 2200 use the plastic piece that is enclosed, as it is in figure 2.');
INSERT INTO `txt_eng` VALUES ('Instrucciones reseteador Universal_2', 'Solution of Problems\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nThe green light does not blink nor ignites. \r\n1. The contacts of the resetter are not in contact with the chip or the chip is dirty \r\n2. If the cartridge is not original of Epson, this could not be compatible with the resetter. \r\n3. If the cartridge is original, the chip could have been deteriorated or Epson has changed the design of the later chip to the manufacture of the chip. \r\n4. Verify the state of the batteries.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nIf the light remains fixes, the cartridge already was rested\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nSubstitution of the batteries\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n1. Unscrew the later cover. \r\n2. Retire with well-taken care of the printed circuit. Replace the batteries and you return to mount the resetter, with taken care of much not to double the contacts.');
